column3: How critical is the problem of operating room waste?
column4: How motivated are you in improving the sustainability of your surgical practice?
column5: How much of a priority should operating room sustainability be for your institution?
column6: How well do you understand the environmental impact of your operations?
column7: How much effort does your institution put into teaching you about operating room sustainability?
column8: How well does the surgical team understand operating room sustainability?
column9: Is it true that reusable items (such as ports) are just as safe as single use items?
column10: Is it true that reprocessed instruments (such as a Ligasure) are just as safe as brand new (OEM) items?
column11: How often does the surgical staff open too many items prior to surgery?
column12: How often do you use the majority of instruments and supplies on your preference card?
column13: Is it true that administrative roadblocks thwart your ability to make sustainable changes?
column14: Are you confident that individual changes you make can have an impact on climate change?
column15: How willing are you to switch from a single use instrument (such as a port) to a reusable instrument?
column16: How willing are you to switch from a brand new (OEM) instrument (such as a Ligasure) to a reprocessed instrument?
column17: How willing are you to switch from a single use surgical gown to a reusable cloth surgical gown?
column18: How willing are you to switch from a single use surgical towels to a reusable surgical towels?
column19: How willing are you to reduce items on preference cards following periodic preference card review?
column20: How willing are you to reduce items on preference cards based on colleagues usage patterns?
column21: How willing are you to participate in a program where the cost and carbon footprint for each surgeon performing a particular operation is displayed?
column22: How willing are you transition completely from water-based to alcohol-based scrub?
column23: How willing are you to reduce the default length of stay for elective patients who are recovering appropriately?
column24: How willing are you to see the majority of routine post-operative patients via telemedicine?
column25: How motivated would you be in improving the sustainability of your practice if you personally received a cash incentive?
column26: How motivated would you be in improving the sustainability of your practice if your division received a cash incentive?
column27: How motivated would you be in improving the sustainability of your practice if you receive a percentage of the cost savings?
column28: How motivated would you be in improving the sustainability of your practice if your division receives additional research funding?
column29: How motivated would you be in improving the sustainability of your practice if you receive a perk (such as free professional membership)?
column30: How motivated would you be in improving the sustainability of your practice if your division receives a perk (such as a pizza party)?
column31: How motivated would you be in improving the sustainability of your practice if you receive personal recognition from your department?
column32: How motivated would you be in improving the sustainability of your practice if your division/group receives recognition from your department?
column33: How motivated would you be in improving the sustainability of your practice if you receive national recognition?
